# Code Review Skill

When invoked with `@code-review`, perform a thorough code review following this structured process.

## Review Process

### 1. Understand the Context
- Identify the files being reviewed
- Understand the purpose of the changes
- Check if changes align with project architecture

### 2. Code Quality Checks

#### Correctness
- [ ] Logic is correct and handles edge cases
- [ ] Error handling is comprehensive
- [ ] Null safety is properly implemented
- [ ] Async/await patterns are correct

#### Performance
- [ ] No unnecessary widget rebuilds
- [ ] Proper use of const constructors
- [ ] Efficient data structures and algorithms
- [ ] No memory leaks (dispose patterns)

#### Security
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or API keys
- [ ] Input validation where needed
- [ ] Proper data sanitization

#### Maintainability
- [ ] Code is readable and self-documenting
- [ ] Functions are focused and not too long
- [ ] Proper separation of concerns
- [ ] No code duplication

#### Flutter-Specific
- [ ] Widget tree is efficient
- [ ] State management is appropriate
- [ ] Navigation patterns are correct
- [ ] Responsive design considerations

